Chlorella cells were washed using DI water and collected by centrifugation (3775 × g, 3 min), and then freeze-dried for 24 h to produce the cell powder. The dried cells were weighed (M1) and immersed in diethyl ether for 16 h and then placed into a Soxhlet extractor for extraction of lipid. The powder was dried and weighed (M2), and the lipid content (N) was calculated by Eq. (1):1N%=M1−M2M1*100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
